{"title":"PruebasHepáticas v3 iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/PruebasHepáticas v3 iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Pruebas Sanguíneas\\NHepáticas Anormales","guid":"sAKOqlclu_2MYNQsyu10Lg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Conceptos\\NFundamentales","guid":"kGyu4d5CdD5zcPsOzsxjsQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"LBT (Liver Blood Tests) → baja sensibilidad y especificidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"NO son pruebas de FUNCIÓN hepática → nombre incorrecto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Resultado anormal = aviso para investigar causa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Riesgo/pronóstico determinado por CAUSA, no por grado de alteración","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"No interpretar de forma AISLADA → siempre con clínica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Cirrosis avanzada puede tener ALT/AST normales → pérdida de tejido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"Resultados anormales raramente se normalizan en <1 mes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"Prevalencia LBT anormales en APS: 21.7% de todas las solicitudes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"0","text":"NUEVA NOMENCLATURA\\NSLD (2023)","guid":"FQyoBKMwU4OPc3YIUb3m8g","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Steatotic Liver Disease (SLD) → término paraguas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"MASLD reemplaza NAFLD (Delphi multisociedad, jun 2023)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"10","text":"MASLD = esteatosis + >=1\\Nfactor riesgo cardiometabólico\\N(de 5 criterios)","guid":"3aKsYchJQ6Vs-cu7I-S3yw","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"Obesidad/sobrepeso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"DM2 o prediabetes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"HTA (>=130/85 o en tratamiento)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"13","text":"Dislipidemia (TG>=1.7, HDL bajo o en tratamiento)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"13","text":"Síndrome metabólico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"10","text":"MASH reemplaza NASH → esteatohepatitis metabólica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"10","text":"MetALD → MASLD +\\Nconsumo moderado-alto\\Nalcohol","guid":"lLcUawv7vF8MSPwuzoeSiw","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Mujeres: 140-350 g/semana (20-50 g/día)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"Hombres: 210-420 g/semana (30-60 g/día)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"10","text":"ALD → predominio alcohol (>350 g/sem mujeres, >420 g/sem hombres)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"10","text":"SLD criptogénica → sin criterios metabólicos ni causa identificable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"10","text":"MASLD y NAFLD son INTERCAMBIABLES: 98-99% de NAFLD cumple criterios MASLD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"10","text":"Diagnóstico POSITIVO (no por exclusión) → cambio conceptual clave","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"0","text":"Panel\\NEstándar","guid":"A3dBcowhdH0MyPsuND0peg","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"ALT (Alanina\\NAminotransferasa)","guid":"MxtnLHLsAfVOsnDLChxX2g","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"Mayor especificidad hepática que AST","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"28","text":"Normal: 1-40 IU/L","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"27","text":"AST (Aspartato\\NAminotransferasa)","guid":"m-wY6AocstfgXorL-BjSCQ","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"Hígado + músculo esquelético + miocardio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"Ratio De Ritis AST:ALT → ver sección específica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"27","text":"ALP (Fosfatasa\\NAlcalina)","guid":"4Dt0FjRFoQdcSQz5nqgYIw","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Células epiteliales biliares + hueso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Normal: 30-130 IU/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"Embarazo y vitamina D baja → elevan ALP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"27","text":"GGT (Gamma-Glutamil\\NTransferasa)","guid":"6iG6aYuFQdWuW6ksRxmZdA","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Hepatocitos (no hueso) → confirma origen hepático de ALP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"GGT elevada = predictor independiente mortalidad por todas las causas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"Elevación leve: HR 1.84 (IC 1.53-2.23)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"38","text":"Elevación severa >=2.5x LSN: HR 6.64 (IC 4.96-8.88)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"27","text":"Bilirrubina","guid":"","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"Normal: <21 umol/L","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"45","parent":"27","text":"Albúmina","guid":"","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"Normal: 35-50 g/L → función sintética","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"27","text":"INR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"Función sintética → elevado = falla hepática","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"27","text":"Plaquetas (FBC)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"Trombocitopenia → complicación daño crónico/cirrosis","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"0","text":"Patrones\\NDiagnósticos","guid":"VpuEEKiH1WOdQmyNkk-D_A","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"1. BILIRRUBINA AISLADA ELEVADA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"Causa más común: Síndrome de Gilbert (5-10% población)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"Menos frecuente: hemólisis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"52","text":"Acción: bilirrubina conjugada/no conjugada en ayunas + FBC + frotis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"52","text":"Si anemia → reticulocitos + LDH","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"51","text":"2. PATRÓN HEPATÍTICO (ALT/AST alt)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"Causas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"MASLD → más prevalente a nivel mundial (38%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"ALD → enfermedad hepática por alcohol","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"Hepatitis viral (B, C)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"58","text":"Hepatitis autoinmune","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"58","text":"Hemocromatosis/sobrecarga hierro","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"58","text":"DILI → daño hepático inducido por fármacos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"57","text":"Acción inicial: GGT + FBC + ecografía hepática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"57","text":"Panel etiológico: HBsAg + Anti-VHC + autoanticuerpos + inmunoglobulinas + ferritina + saturación transferrina + HbA1c","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"57","text":"Ratio De Ritis AST:ALT","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":">1 → fibrosis avanzada/cirrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"En alcohol: AST > ALT (alcohol agota piridoxina → limita síntesis ALT)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Ratio >1 → elastografía obligatoria","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"51","text":"3. PATRÓN COLESTÁSICO (ALP/GGT alt)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"Causas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"Obstrucción biliar → cálculos, neoplasia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"Congestión hepática → falla cardíaca derecha","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"DILI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"Colangitis biliar primaria (CBP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"72","text":"Colangitis esclerosante primaria (CEP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"72","text":"Deficiencia vitamina D → ALP aislada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"71","text":"Acción: ecografía hepática → buscar dilatación ductos/lesiones focales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"71","text":"GGT normal + ALP alta → sospechar origen ÓSEO (no hepático)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"51","text":"4. FALLA SINTÉTICA / MALIGNIDAD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"Albúmina baja + INR elevado ± ictericia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"Causas: malignidad, falla cardíaca, ERC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"81","text":"Acción: ecografía URGENTE + derivación URGENTE hepatología","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"85","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"MASLD: 38% prevalencia global (IC 95% 33.71-42.49)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"ALD Europa: 5.4% (IC 95% 3.9-7.1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"85","text":"Hepatitis B global: 3.8% (IC 95% 3.0-5.0)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"85","text":"Hepatitis C global: 0.8% (IC 95% 0.6-1.0)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"85","text":"Enfermedad hepática crónica = 8va causa de AVAD en hombres","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"0","text":"Algoritmo de Manejo (5 Pasos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"PASO 1: Evaluación clínica inicial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Riesgo hepatitis, medicamentos, alcohol, trasplante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"Factores riesgo: síndrome metabólico, DM2, obesidad, HF enfermedad hepática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"92","text":"RED FLAGS → derivar mismo día","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Albúmina en caída","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"Enzimas >=2.5x LSN","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"95","text":"Ictericia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"95","text":"Signos malignidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"92","text":"Alcohol: usar AUDIT-C (cribado positivo >=5 puntos)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"91","text":"PASO 2: Identificar patrón (ver sección Patrones)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"91","text":"PASO 3: Pruebas adicionales según patrón","guid":"","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"Estándar: HBsAg + Anti-VHC + HbA1c + autoanticuerpos + inmunoglobulinas + ferritina + saturación transferrina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"102","text":"Extendido: anticuerpos celíacos + genética hemocromatosis + Alfa-1 antitripsina + TSH + ceruloplasmina + cobre urinario","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"91","text":"PASO 4: Diagnóstico diferencial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Gilbert / Hemólisis / MASLD / ALD / MetALD / DILI / Malignidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"91","text":"PASO 5: Manejo y derivación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"0","text":"Etiologías Específicas y Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"Síndrome de Gilbert","guid":"","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"Bilirrubina NO conjugada elevada persistente + otras pruebas normales + sin anemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"109","text":"Variante genética benigna → 5-10% europeos occidentales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"109","text":"Ictericia intermitente: estrés, ayuno, infección","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"109","text":"BENIGNO → no requiere monitoreo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"109","text":"Estatinas con precaución → mayor riesgo efectos adversos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"108","text":"MASLD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Diagnóstico: esteatosis (eco o histología) + >=1 factor riesgo cardiometabólico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"Prevalencia global 30-38% adultos (en aumento paralelo a obesidad)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"MASH (esteatohepatitis) → forma progresiva → riesgo fibrosis/cirrosis/CHC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"115","text":"Manejo: tratar causa subyacente + riesgo CV + progresión con FIB-4","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"115","text":"Fármacos metabólicos con evidencia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"Inhibidores SGLT-2 → mejoran esteatosis + riesgo CV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"120","text":"Agonistas GLP-1 → semaglutide (ESSENCE trial: mejora fibrosis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"120","text":"Tirzepatida → reduce esteatohepatitis y fibrosis (fase 2)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"120","text":"Pioglitazona y vitamina E → mejoran esteatohepatitis (no en cirrosis)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"115","text":"RESMETIROM (Rezdiffra) → PRIMER FÁRMACO FDA aprobado para MASH","guid":"","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"Aprobación acelerada FDA: 14 marzo 2024","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"Agonista selectivo receptor tiroides beta (THR-beta)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"125","text":"Indicación: MASH no cirrótico con fibrosis F2-F3","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"125","text":"Dosis: 80 mg/día (<100 kg) o 100 mg/día (>=100 kg)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"125","text":"Eficacia (MAESTRO-NASH): resolución MASH 26-30% vs 10% placebo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"125","text":"Mejora fibrosis >=1 estadio: 24-26% vs 14% placebo (p<0.001)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"125","text":"NO requiere biopsia previa para iniciar → usar NITs (FIB-4 + VCTE)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"125","text":"Interacción: inhibidores CYP2C8 (ajustar dosis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"125","text":"Límites estatinas concomitantes (ej. atorvastatina máx 40 mg/día)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"125","text":"COSTO: ~47.400 USD/año → barrera acceso global","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"115","text":"Intervención: dieta + cese tabaco + pérdida de peso >=7-10%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"108","text":"ALD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Mujeres: >50 g/día (>35 U/semana)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"Hombres: >60 g/día (>50 U/semana)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"137","text":"Meta: abstinencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"137","text":"ALT/AST NO son indicadores fiables de fibrosis en ALD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"137","text":"Referir a elastografía transitoria","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"108","text":"MetALD (zona gris metabólico-alcohol)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"Mujeres: 20-50 g/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"Hombres: 30-60 g/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"143","text":"Manejo CV + moderación alcohol","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"108","text":"DILI (Daño Hepático por Fármacos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"Diagnóstico de exclusión → alta sospecha clínica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"Fármacos más frecuentes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Antimicrobianos (amoxicilina-clavulánico → causa más común)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"Suplementos herbales y dietéticos → creciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"Anticancerosos (inhibidores tirosina kinasa, inmunocheck-point)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"149","text":"AINEs, paracetamol","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"149","text":"Estatinas → daño idiosincrático raro pero posible","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"155","parent":"147","text":"Criterios diagnósticos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"Relación temporal con inicio del fármaco","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"Exclusión otras etiologías (hepatitis viral, autoinmune, biliar)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"RUCAM (Roussel Uclaf Causality Assessment Method) → algoritmo gold standard","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"147","text":"Patrón hepatocelular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"ALT >=5x LSN y/o ratio R >=5 (R = [ALT/LSN] / [ALP/LSN])","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"Mortalidad hepatocelular con ictericia: ~10% (Hy's Law)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"147","text":"Patrón colestásico → ALP >=2x LSN y ratio R <2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"147","text":"Patrón mixto → 2 < R < 5","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"147","text":"MANEJO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"165","parent":"164","text":"Retirar fármaco causante → inmediato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"164","text":"Observación estrecha","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"164","text":"ICTERICIA + coagulopatía → hospitalización urgente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"164","text":"Corticoides → controversiales, solo si no distinguible de hepatitis autoinmune","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"164","text":"Referir a hepatología si jaundice + coagulopatía o falla hepática","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"108","text":"Estatinas en enfermedad hepática","guid":"","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"SEGURAS si ALT/AST <3x LSN","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"Asociadas a mejoría de inflamación, esteatosis y fibrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"No suspender automáticamente ante transaminasas leves","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"0","text":"Evaluación de Fibrosis: FIB-4","guid":"","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"Fórmula: edad × AST / (plaquetas × raíz cuadrada ALT)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"Desarrollado originalmente en VIH/VHC (Sterling et al.)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"174","text":"AUROC 0.765 para F3-F4 en cohorte original","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"174","text":"FIB-4 <1.3 → bajo riesgo → reevaluar cada 1-3 años","guid":"","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"Con DM2/prediabetes o >=2 factores metabólicos → reevaluar cada 1-2 años","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"174","text":"FIB-4 1.3-2.67 → riesgo intermedio → evaluación secundaria (FibroScan o ELF)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"174","text":"FIB-4 >2.67 → alto riesgo → DERIVAR hepatología","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"174","text":"FIB-4 >3.48 → sugestivo cirrosis (AASLD 2023)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"174","text":"LIMITACIONES CRÍTICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"184","parent":"183","text":"Poder predictivo REDUCIDO en >65 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"183","text":"También reducido en <35 años y DM2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"183","text":"Especificidad para fibrosis avanzada <30% en >65 años → FALSOS POSITIVOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"183","text":"En >65 años: umbral bajo intermedio ajustado a FIB-4 2.0","guid":"","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"<2.0 → bajo riesgo (EASL-EASD-EASO 2024, AASLD 2023)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"187","text":"2.0-2.67 → riesgo intermedio → VCTE o ELF","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"187","text":">2.67 → alto riesgo → hepatología","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"191","parent":"183","text":"Debate activo: estudio canadiense (n=985) sugiere que el umbral 1.3 mantiene VPN 100% para VCTE >=10 kPa en >65 años → no habría necesidad de subir umbral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"183","text":"CONCLUSIÓN práctica: en AM usar FIB-4 con cautela + confirmar con VCTE si >1.3","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"174","text":"Herramientas secundarias si FIB-4 indeterminado","guid":"","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"VCTE (FibroScan) → preferida → menor validez en obesidad severa y FA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"ELF (Enhanced Liver Fibrosis) → alternativa en obesidad o marcapasos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"MR-elastografía → más precisa, costosa, limitada disponibilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"193","text":"FAST score (FibroScan + AST) → identifica MASH activo con fibrosis","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"0","text":"Cirrosis Hepática — Concepto y Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"Histología → regeneración nodular + septos fibrosos → distorsión vascular → HTP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"FASE COMPENSADA → supervivencia media >12 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"198","text":"FASE DESCOMPENSADA → supervivencia media ~2 años (mortalidad 20%/año)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"198","text":"Mortalidad: 5x mayor (compensada) vs 10x mayor (descompensada) vs población general","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"198","text":"Prevalencia global descompensación: 5.2M (1990) → 10.6M (2017)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"198","text":"Transición compensada→descompensada: 5-12% anual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"198","text":"ACLF (Acute-on-Chronic Liver Failure)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"Forma más grave de descompensación aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"Prevalencia en cirrótico hospitalizado: ~35%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"205","text":"Mortalidad a 90 días: 58%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"209","parent":"198","text":"Nuevos conceptos descompensación (CANONIC, PREDICT, ACLARA)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"210","parent":"209","text":"Descompensación No Aguda (DNA): sin inflamación sistémica severa → mortalidad 12m: 18.3%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"209","text":"Descompensación Aguda (DA): hemorragia, ascitis, EH, infección → mortalidad 12m: 68.8%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"198","text":"DIAGNÓSTICO — Pruebas No Invasivas (NILDA)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"FIB-4 (ver sección específica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"212","text":"Elastografía de transición (FibroScan)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"EXCLUIR HPCS: LSM ≤15 kPa + plaquetas ≥150 × 10⁹/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"214","text":"INCLUIR HPCS: LSM >25 kPa (independiente de plaquetas)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"217","parent":"212","text":"Screening várices: se puede omitir endoscopia si LSM <20 kPa + plaquetas ≥150.000","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"212","text":"Biopsia hepática → gold standard, solo para casos de etiología incierta","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"198","text":"PUNTUACIONES PRONÓSTICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"Child-Pugh","guid":"","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"Clase A (5-6 pts) / Clase B (7-9 pts) / Clase C (10-15 pts)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"220","text":"Variables: encefalopatía, ascitis, bilirrubina, albúmina, TP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"223","parent":"219","text":"MELD → predice mortalidad 90 días","guid":"","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"Bilirrubina + creatinina + INR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"225","parent":"219","text":"MELD-Na → incorpora sodio sérico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"219","text":"MELD 3.0 → añade sexo femenino + albúmina → mayor equidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"227","parent":"226","text":"Útil cuando creatinina subestima falla renal (sarcopenia)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"228","parent":"219","text":"CLIF-C ADs: <45 pts → mortalidad 3m 1.8%; ≥60 pts → 31%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"229","parent":"0","text":"Cirrosis — Complicaciones y Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"230","parent":"229","text":"HIPERTENSIÓN PORTAL (HTP)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"GPVH normal: <5 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"HTP clínicamente significativa (HPCS): GPVH ≥10 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"230","text":"Hemorragia varicosa: GPVH >12 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"230","text":"Fisiopatología: HTP → vasodilatación esplácnica (NO) → circulación hiperdinámica → activación SRAA/SNS","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"229","text":"BETABLOQUEANTES NO SELECTIVOS (BBNS) en HTP","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"CARVEDILOL → elección (antagonismo alfa-1 adicional, vasodilatación intrahepática)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"237","parent":"236","text":"Inicio: 6.25 mg/día → escalar a 12.5 mg/día tras 3 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"236","text":"Sin objetivo de FC; objetivo PAS ≥90 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"239","parent":"235","text":"Propranolol: inicio 20-40 mg c/12h; objetivo FC 55-60 lpm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"235","text":"Nadolol: inicio 20-40 mg noche; objetivo FC 55-60 lpm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"235","text":"CONTRAINDICAR si: hiponatremia severa (Na <120), PAS <90 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"242","parent":"229","text":"ASCITIS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"243","parent":"242","text":"Evento descompensador más frecuente (5-10% anual)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"242","text":"SAAG (Gradiente Albúmina Suero-Ascitis)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"245","parent":"244","text":"SAAG ≥1.1 g/dL → HTP (precisión 97%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"244","text":"SAAG <1.1 g/dL → descarta HTP (otras causas: malignidad, TBC, pancreatitis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"244","text":"ICC derecha → SAAG ≥1.1 + proteínas ascíticas >2.5 g/dL","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"248","parent":"242","text":"Diagnóstico PBE: PMN ascítico >250/mm³ → tratar sin esperar cultivos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"242","text":"Tratamiento ascitis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"250","parent":"249","text":"Restricción sodio <2 g/día (90 mmol/día)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"249","text":"Espironolactona 100 mg + furosemida 40 mg (ratio 100:40)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"249","text":"Dosis máximas: espironolactona 400 mg / furosemida 160 mg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"249","text":"Pérdida peso objetivo: 0.5 kg/día (sin edema) / 1.0 kg/día (con edema)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"254","parent":"242","text":"Paracentesis gran volumen (>5 L) → albúmina 6-8 g/L extraído","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"242","text":"Albúmina en frágil/hipotenso/AKI: considerar incluso si <5 L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"242","text":"Ascitis refractaria → TIPS o alfapump","guid":"","children":[{"id":"257","parent":"256","text":"TIPS: superior a paracentesis, mejora supervivencia libre de trasplante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"256","text":"MELD >18 → mala candidatura a TIPS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"256","text":"EH post-TIPS hasta 50% → precaución en AM >70a y sarcopénicos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"260","parent":"229","text":"HIDROTÓRAX HEPÁTICO (HH)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"261","parent":"260","text":"Mortalidad a 1 año: 20-50% (4x mayor que ascitis refractaria)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"260","text":"Toracocentesis terapéutica → alivio síntomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"263","parent":"260","text":"NUNCA colocar tubo de tórax → alta morbilidad y mortalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"260","text":"HH refractario → catéteres pleurales tunelizados (paliativo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"265","parent":"229","text":"HEMORRAGIA VARICOSA AGUDA (HVA)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"266","parent":"265","text":"Mortalidad a 6 semanas: 10-15%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"267","parent":"265","text":"Estrategia restrictiva: transfundir si Hb <7 g/dL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"265","text":"Fármacos vasoactivos: terlipresina, somatostatina, octreótido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"269","parent":"265","text":"Endoscopia urgente (<12-24h) con ligadura endoscópica (LEV)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"265","text":"Antibióticos profilácticos: ceftriaxona","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"265","text":"TIPS precoz (<72h): si Child-Pugh C 10-13 o Child-Pugh B >7 con sangrado activo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"272","parent":"229","text":"ENCEFALOPATÍA HEPÁTICA (EH)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"273","parent":"272","text":"Prevalencia en cirrosis: 30-40%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"274","parent":"272","text":"Clasificación West Haven","guid":"","children":[{"id":"275","parent":"274","text":"Grado 0-1: EH encubierta → Gold standard: PHES","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"276","parent":"274","text":"Animal Naming Test: <15 animales/min → screening cabecera","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"277","parent":"274","text":"Grado 2-4: EH manifiesta","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"278","parent":"272","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"279","parent":"278","text":"Primera línea: lactulosa (disacárido no absorbible)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"280","parent":"278","text":"Adjunto: rifaximina (mantener remisión)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"281","parent":"278","text":"Suplementos de zinc","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"282","parent":"278","text":"NO restringir proteínas a largo plazo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"283","parent":"229","text":"PERITONITIS BACTERIANA ESPONTÁNEA (PBE)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"284","parent":"283","text":"1/3 de hospitalizados con cirrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"283","text":"Hasta 1/3 asintomáticos → paracentesis obligatoria en TODO ingreso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"286","parent":"283","text":"PMN >250/mm³ → tratar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"287","parent":"283","text":"Tratamiento: ceftriaxona 2 g/día + albúmina IV (1.5 g/kg día 1 + 1 g/kg día 3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"288","parent":"283","text":"Bacterias MDR: ~35% de infecciones en cirrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"289","parent":"283","text":"Profilaxis 2ª: TMP-SMX o ciprofloxacino","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"290","parent":"229","text":"SÍNDROME HEPATORRENAL (SHR-LRA)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"291","parent":"290","text":"Diagnóstico de exclusión: LRA sin mejoría tras albúmina 1 g/kg y retiro diuréticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"292","parent":"290","text":"Tratamiento: terlipresina + albúmina (primera línea)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"293","parent":"290","text":"Terlipresina: riesgo insuficiencia respiratoria → monitoreo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"294","parent":"290","text":"Tratamiento definitivo: trasplante hepático","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"295","parent":"229","text":"HIPONATREMIA EN CIRROSIS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"296","parent":"295","text":"Hipervolémica dilucional en 90% de casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"297","parent":"295","text":"Criterio: Na <130 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"298","parent":"295","text":"Manejo ambulatorio: restricción hídrica 1-1.5 L/día si Na <125","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"299","parent":"295","text":"Manejo hospitalario: suspender diuréticos/BB + albúmina IV ± vasoconstrictores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"300","parent":"295","text":"Salina hipertónica 3%: solo en amenaza vital o pre-trasplante, corrección lenta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"301","parent":"295","text":"BETA-BLOQUEANTES: suspender si PAS <90 mmHg o hiponatremia severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"302","parent":"229","text":"SARCOPENIA EN CIRROSIS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"303","parent":"302","text":"Prevalencia: 20-40% compensada; >40-70% descompensada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"304","parent":"302","text":"Predictor independiente mortalidad, EH e infecciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"305","parent":"302","text":"Manejo: proteínas 1.2-1.5 g/kg/día + snack nocturno + ejercicio","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"306","parent":"229","text":"TIPS (Transjugular Intrahepatic Portosystemic Shunt)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"307","parent":"306","text":"Indicaciones: ascitis refractaria, HH, HVA de alto riesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"308","parent":"306","text":"Contraindicaciones absolutas: ICC, HTP pulmonar severa, EH no controlada, sepsis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"309","parent":"306","text":"Precaución: edad >70 años, MELD >18, sarcopenia severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"310","parent":"229","text":"TRASPLANTE HEPÁTICO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"311","parent":"310","text":"Única terapia curativa para cirrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"312","parent":"310","text":"Considerar en TODOS con ascitis/HH sin importar MELD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"313","parent":"310","text":"MELD 3.0 mejoró equidad de asignación (incorpora sexo y albúmina)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"314","parent":"0","text":"MASLD — Riesgo Cardiovascular (Perspectiva Cardio-Geriátrica)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"315","parent":"314","text":"MASLD como enfermedad MULTISISTÉMICA → no solo hepática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"316","parent":"314","text":"Riesgo CV en MASLD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"317","parent":"316","text":"Metaanálisis 34 estudios (>500.000 individuos): ↑64% mortalidad cardiovascular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"318","parent":"316","text":"OR 1.27-1.66 para IAM, ACV isquémico, FA, IC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"319","parent":"316","text":"HFpEF: riesgo 2.59x mayor (principalmente IC con FE preservada)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"320","parent":"316","text":"FA: HR 1.21; recurrencia post-ablación mayor si fibrosis avanzada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"321","parent":"316","text":"Calcificación coronaria en Framingham Heart Study (asociación independiente)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"322","parent":"314","text":"Mecanismos fisiopatológicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"323","parent":"322","text":"Inflamación sistémica: TNF-α, IL-6, IL-1β","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"324","parent":"322","text":"Estrés oxidativo + ROS → disfunción eNOS → ↓NO → vasoconstricción","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"325","parent":"322","text":"Resistencia insulínica → ↑rigidez arterial → aterosclerosis precoz","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"326","parent":"322","text":"Dislipidemia aterogénica: ↑VLDL, ↑LDL pequeñas y densas, ↓HDL funcional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"327","parent":"322","text":"Disbiosis intestinal + TMAO → activación TLR4 → inflamación hepática y vascular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"328","parent":"314","text":"FIBROSIS como predictor CV más fuerte","guid":"","children":[{"id":"329","parent":"328","text":"FIB-4 ≥2.67: mortalidad CV HR 2.96; mortalidad total HR 1.64 (cohorte >46.000)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"330","parent":"328","text":"Fibrosis → no incluida aún en SCORE2/ASCVD → brecha diagnóstica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"331","parent":"314","text":"Fármacos con beneficio dual (hepático + CV)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"332","parent":"331","text":"GLP-1 RA (semaglutida, liraglutida) → primera línea si DM2/obesidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"333","parent":"331","text":"SGLT-2i → beneficio renal, CV y hepático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"334","parent":"331","text":"Estatinas → seguras; mejoran fibrosis y reducen eventos CV","guid":"","children":[{"id":"335","parent":"334","text":"No suspender por elevaciones ALT/AST <3x LSN","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"336","parent":"331","text":"Pioglitazona → mejora fibrosis/esteatosis; precaución retención líquidos en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"337","parent":"314","text":"HFpEF en MASLD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"338","parent":"337","text":"Niveles NTproBNP pueden estar ATENUADOS → diagnóstico tardío","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"339","parent":"337","text":"Ecocardiografía ante disnea/fatiga en MASLD","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"340","parent":"0","text":"Criterios de Derivación Urgente","guid":"","children":[{"id":"341","parent":"340","text":"Paciente agudamente enfermo con riesgo falla hepática aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"342","parent":"340","text":"Sospecha sobrecarga hierro primaria, malignidad o falla sintética","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"343","parent":"340","text":"LBT >=2.5x LSN","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"344","parent":"340","text":"FIB-4 >2.67 (o >2.0 si >65 años)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"345","parent":"0","text":"Manejo Multidisciplinario","guid":"","children":[{"id":"346","parent":"345","text":"Farmacéutico → revisión interacciones + sospecha DILI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"347","parent":"345","text":"Nutricionista → dieta, enfermedad celíaca","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"348","parent":"345","text":"Servicios manejo de peso → GLP-1 si aplica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"349","parent":"345","text":"Revisión ANUAL → signos descompensación (encefalopatía, ascitis, sarcopenia)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"350","parent":"0","text":"Hígado en el Adulto Mayor (Perspectiva Geriátrica)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"351","parent":"350","text":"CAMBIOS FISIOLÓGICOS con el envejecimiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"352","parent":"351","text":"Reducción de masa hepática (~20-40% a los 80 años)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"353","parent":"351","text":"Reducción flujo sanguíneo hepático (~40%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"354","parent":"351","text":"Disminución CYP450 → metabolismo farmacológico enlentecido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"355","parent":"351","text":"Albúmina tiende a bajar fisiológicamente → no siempre indica falla","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"356","parent":"351","text":"ALT puede estar MÁS BAJA que en adultos jóvenes con misma lesión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"357","parent":"350","text":"MASLD en AM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"358","parent":"357","text":"Prevalencia 40.3% en 60-74 años (mayor que en jóvenes)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"359","parent":"357","text":"Mayor prevalencia de fibrosis avanzada asociada a mayor edad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"360","parent":"357","text":"Mayor riesgo cardiovascular concomitante → priorizar evaluación CV","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"361","parent":"350","text":"DILI en AM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"362","parent":"361","text":"Mayor riesgo por polifarmacia y farmacocinética alterada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"363","parent":"361","text":"Deprescripción como estrategia preventiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"364","parent":"361","text":"Estatinas: seguras con ALT/AST <3x LSN → no suspender por inercia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"365","parent":"350","text":"FIB-4 en AM → ver sección específica de evaluación de fibrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"366","parent":"350","text":"Sarcopenia + enfermedad hepática","guid":"","children":[{"id":"367","parent":"366","text":"Sarcopenia frecuente en cirrosis → empeora pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"368","parent":"366","text":"Albúmina baja puede reflejar sarcopenia, no solo falla sintética hepática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"369","parent":"366","text":"Circunferencia pantorrilla + fuerza prensil → complementar interpretación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"370","parent":"350","text":"Consideraciones especiales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"371","parent":"370","text":"Valorar siempre polifarmacia antes de solicitar nuevos estudios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"372","parent":"370","text":"Hemólisis más frecuente en AM → descartar en bilirrubina aislada elevada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"373","parent":"370","text":"ICC derecha → causa frecuente de patrón colestásico en AM → ecocardiograma","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"374","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"375","parent":"374","text":"ALT normal NO descarta cirrosis → pérdida de tejido hepático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"376","parent":"374","text":"FIB-4 en >65a: umbral intermedio ajustado a FIB-4 2.0 (AASLD 2023, EASL 2024)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"377","parent":"374","text":"Nunca repetir LBT anormales esperando normalización espontánea → primero establecer causa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"378","parent":"374","text":"GGT elevada = predictor mortalidad por todas las causas (HR 6.64 severa)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"379","parent":"374","text":"AST:ALT >1 → fibrosis/cirrosis → elastografía obligatoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"380","parent":"374","text":"Estatinas SEGURAS con ALT/AST <3x LSN → no suspender por inercia + mejoran MASLD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"381","parent":"374","text":"ALP aislada alta → descartar vitamina D baja ANTES de cascada biliar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"382","parent":"374","text":"Gilbert + estatinas → mayor riesgo efectos adversos → prescribir con precaución","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"383","parent":"374","text":"50% de LBT anormales en APS NO reciben seguimiento → oportunidad perdida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"384","parent":"374","text":"Patrón mixto (hepatítico + colestásico) es frecuente → correlación clínica cruzada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"385","parent":"374","text":"MASLD ≈ NAFLD → 98-99% intercambiables → evidencia previa sigue siendo válida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"386","parent":"374","text":"Resmetirom (2024): PRIMER fármaco FDA para MASH F2-F3 → THR-beta agonista","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"387","parent":"374","text":"ICC derecha → buscar en patrón colestásico en adulto mayor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"388","parent":"374","text":"ALT puede ser artificialmente BAJA en AM → no subestimar lesión real","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"389","parent":"374","text":"DILI en AM: polifarmacia = principal factor de riesgo → revisar STOPP/START","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"390","parent":"374","text":"SAAG ≥1.1 g/dL: precisión 97% para HTP → siempre solicitar en paracentesis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"391","parent":"374","text":"PBE asintomática hasta 1/3 casos → paracentesis diagnóstica en TODO ingreso cirrótico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"392","parent":"374","text":"Regla 100:40 (espironolactona:furosemida) → mantiene normopotasemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"393","parent":"374","text":"NUNCA tubo de tórax en hidrotórax hepático → mortalidad alta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"394","parent":"374","text":"TIPS >70a o sarcopénico → riesgo EH post-TIPS 50% → evaluar calidad de vida previamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"395","parent":"374","text":"Carvedilol = BBNS de elección en HTP (no requiere titulación por FC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"396","parent":"374","text":"Beta-bloqueantes: SUSPENDER si PAS <90 mmHg o Na <120 mEq/L en cirrosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"397","parent":"374","text":"MASLD → sospechar HFpEF aunque NTproBNP sea normal (niveles atenuados)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"398","parent":"374","text":"Fibrosis hepática NO incluida en SCORE2/ASCVD → brecha importante en riesgo CV real","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"399","parent":"374","text":"GLP-1 RA + SGLT2i: beneficio dual hepático + cardiovascular en MASLD con DM2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"400","parent":"374","text":"Animal Naming Test (<15 animales/min): screening rápido EH encubierta en cabecera","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"401","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"402","parent":"401","text":"1. Stewart S, Distante S, Duke N, Shearman J. Interpreting abnormal liver blood test results. BMJ. 2025;391:e082648.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"403","parent":"401","text":"2. Rinella ME, Neuschwander-Tetri BA, Siddiqui MS, et al. AASLD Practice Guidance on NAFLD/MASLD. Hepatology. 2023;77(5):1797-835.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"404","parent":"401","text":"3. Lazarus JV, et al. A multisociety Delphi consensus statement on new fatty liver disease nomenclature. Hepatology. 2023;78(6):1966-86. PMID 37363821.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"405","parent":"401","text":"4. EASL-EASD-EASO. Clinical Practice Guidelines on MASLD. J Hepatol. 2024;81:492-542.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"406","parent":"401","text":"5. Chalasani NP, et al. ACG Clinical Guideline: Diagnosis and Management of Idiosyncratic DILI. Am J Gastroenterol. 2021;116(5):878-98.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"407","parent":"401","text":"6. Harrison SA, et al. Resmetirom (MAESTRO-NASH trial). N Engl J Med. 2024;390(6):497-509.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"408","parent":"401","text":"7. Kasper P, Tacke F, Heppner HJ, Michels G. Liver dysfunction in geriatric patients. Z Gerontol Geriatr. 2022;55(6):519-30.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"409","parent":"401","text":"8. Younossi ZM, Paik JM, et al. Clinical profiles and mortality rates similar for MASLD and NAFLD. J Hepatol. 2024;80(5):694-701.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"410","parent":"401","text":"9. Björnsson ES. Clinical management of drug-induced liver injury (DILI). United European Gastroenterol J. 2021;9(7):781-86.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"411","parent":"401","text":"10. Hosack T, Damry D, Biswas S. Drug-induced liver injury: a comprehensive review. Therap Adv Gastroenterol. 2023;16:17562848231163410.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"412","parent":"401","text":"11. Orman ES, Fortune BE, John BV, Asrani SK. AGA Clinical Practice Update on the Management of Ascites, Volume Overload, and Hyponatremia in Cirrhosis. Gastroenterology. 2025 (In Press).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"413","parent":"401","text":"12. Pose E, Albillos A, Fuster J, et al. Cirrhosis: causes, pathogenesis, history, complications and clinical scores. J Hepatol. 2025 (Guía Drive INGER).","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":413,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"PruebasHepáticas v3 iPad","id":"map_844","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"PruebasHepáticas v3 iPad"}